div1.p: Territory of Washington Third Judicial District } ss. No.4704
To the Sheriff of Pierce County, Greeting:

WHEREAS, C. W. Hutchinson recovered judgment against W. H. Harris, in the District Court for the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding terms at Seattle, on the 13th day of November A.D. 1885 for the sum of costs of Suit Dollars, with interest at the rate of until paid, and cost of suit, amounting to Seventeen and 40/100 ($17.40) Dollars.

THEREFORE, in the name of the United States of America, you are hereby commanded forthwith to levy upon, seize and take into execution, the personal property of the said W.H. Harris in your County, sufficient subject to execution to satisfy said judgment, interest and increaed interest, cost and increased cost, and make sale thereof according to law; and if sufficient personal property cannot be found, then you are further commanded to make the amount of said judgment, interest and increased interest, cost and increased cost, out of his real property, not exempt by law, and make return of this writ within sixty days from the date hereof.
Herein fail not and have you then and there this writ
WITNESS the Hon. Roger S. Greene, Chief Justice of the Supreme Court, and Judge of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, and the Seal of said Court, this 13th day of November A.D. 1885
By James P. Ludlow Deputy Clerk.
IN THE DISTRICT COURT, THIRD JUDICIAL DISTRICT.
C. W. Hutchinson VS. W. H. Harris
Judgment for - - -$ Costs Interest at per cent, $ Increased Interest, - - $ Cost, - - - - - $17.40 Clerk's Incresed Costs, - $ 1.70 Sherif's Increased Costs, - $
Filed Dec 3 1885 James Seavey, Clerk. By James P Ludlow Received Nov 13 1885
